id: aic-python-guidelines
type: language
owner: lead-engineer
extends: project.intent

language: python
version: ">=3.10"

patterns:
  - CLI framework is Typer — no argparse, no Click, no custom argument parsing
  - YAML parsing via PyYAML — no custom parsers
  - Rich library for all terminal output — no raw print statements for UI
  - All AI provider calls go through /providers/ adapter layer only
  - No direct API calls outside the adapter layer ever

structure:
  - /aic
      - /commands      ← one file per CLI command
      - /providers     ← one file per AI provider adapter
      - /core          ← shared logic, file parsing, inheritance resolution
      - /models        ← data models and schemas
      - /utils         ← stateless utility functions only
  - /business          ← business intent files
  - /tests             ← mirrors /aic structure exactly

practices:
  - Type hints mandatory on every function signature
  - Docstring mandatory on every public function
  - No function longer than 30 lines — split if needed
  - No nested conditionals deeper than 3 levels — extract to function
  - All file paths use pathlib.Path — no raw string paths ever
  - All YAML loaded via safe_load — never full load
  - Environment variables loaded via python-dotenv — no os.environ direct access
  - All errors are explicit custom exceptions — no bare except clauses
  - No mutable default arguments ever

security:
  - API keys loaded from environment only — never hardcoded
  - API keys never logged, never in error messages, never in tracebacks
  - All file writes validated against project root — no path traversal
  - No eval, no exec, no subprocess with shell=True ever

testing:
  - pytest for all tests
  - Every public function has at least one test
  - Every failure mode has a dedicated test
  - Mocks for all AI provider calls — no real API calls in tests
  - Test file mirrors source file name — test_init_command.py for init_command.py

dependencies:
  required:
    - typer          ← CLI framework
    - pyyaml         ← YAML parsing
    - rich           ← terminal output
    - python-dotenv  ← environment variable loading
    - httpx          ← HTTP client for provider calls
  optional:
    - anthropic      ← Claude provider
    - google-generativeai ← Gemini provider
    - ollama         ← local model support

error-handling:
  - Every command catches exceptions at the top level
  - User facing errors printed via Rich in red with clear message
  - Technical errors logged to .aic/logs/ never to terminal
  - Exit codes are explicit — 0 success, 1 user error, 2 system error